This is beneficial for identifying the global structure and connectivity of the representational space.

Moving from the lower left to the upper right corner of the parameter space (increasing both \( l \) and \( u \)) shifts the emphasis from local to global relationships. Small \( l \) and \( u \) values highlight local neighbor relationships, while large \( l \) and \( u \) values emphasize the global structure of the representation.
